course_metadata.title: Determination of the technical condition of a typical residential building and forecast of the period of use. Digital 3D assessment of constructions geometrical, mechanical and physical properties, sensors, laboratory research

content_chunks.content: This course offers an in-depth exploration of building condition assessment with a focus on residential structures. Students will gain foundational knowledge in structural analysis, construction materials, and the durability and lifespan of building components. The course covers both traditional and modern assessment techniques, including non-destructive testing (NDT), digital 3D modeling, and Building Information Modeling (BIM). Students will also learn about advanced technologies such as photogrammetry, sensors, thermal imaging, and vibration analysis for effective monitoring of structural integrity. Emphasis is placed on understanding the physical, thermal, acoustic, and moisture properties of materials and their impact on building performance. By the end of the course, students will be equipped to conduct comprehensive building assessments, forecast building lifespan, and develop effective maintenance and management plans to ensure indoor environmental quality and energy efficiency.

Technology for advanced building condition assessment and digital structural analysis - this course delivers comprehensive expertise in building condition assessment and structural analysis methods using cutting-edge residential building evaluation and construction materials testing techniques. Students will master material durability analysis, building lifespan forecasting, and non-destructive testing (NDT) methodologies for optimal digital 3D modeling and Building Information Modeling (BIM) implementation. The curriculum focuses on practical 3D laser scanning applications, photogrammetry utilization, and building monitoring sensors deployment for comprehensive IoT building systems and thermal imaging analysis. Participants will gain hands-on experience with infrared thermography techniques, vibration analysis methods, and structural health monitoring systems for effective moisture detection and material property testing. The program emphasizes indoor environmental quality assessment, energy performance evaluation, and building maintenance planning for geometric property analysis, mechanical property testing, and physical property assessment of building components.
